t-medium"><strong>About Bolt</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt is a full-service <strong>Design + Build</strong> firm and fully insured <strong>General Contractor</strong> based in Brooklyn. We specialize in design-forward hospitality, retail, and residential projects that merge classical sensibility with innovative construction and fabrication methods. We believe that great design is only as strong as its execution — and that means being just as rigorous about budgets, schedules, and communication as we are about creative vision.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium"><strong>The Role</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt Builds is seeking a thoughtful, detail-oriented <strong>Interior Designer</strong> with 2–5 years of experience to join our design and construction team. This role is ideal for someone who is ready to take on more ownership within a fast-paced design-build studio, contributing meaningfully to projects from early concept through construction.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">You will work closely with senior designers and project managers while also operating independently on key deliverables. This role requires both strong design sensibility and the ability to execute. You will move fluidly between creative development, technical documentation, and real-world problem-solving.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium"><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>Design Development &amp; Execution</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Lead and contribute to design concepts across multiple projects, from schematic design through design development</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Produce drawings, 3D models, and renderings using <strong>Rhino, Revit, and Adobe Creative Suite</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Translate conceptual ideas into clear, buildable design solutions</p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>FF&amp;E Selection &amp; Documentation</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Research, select, and specify materials, finishes, and furnishings aligned with project budgets and design intent</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Own and maintain FF&amp;E schedules and supporting documentation</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Coordinate directly with vendors for pricing, lead times, and sample procurement</p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>Project Documentation</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Develop and manage drawing sets throughout design and construction phases</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Coordinate with internal teams and external consultants (AOR, MEP, fabricators, etc.)</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Ensure documentation is clear, organized, and aligned with Bolt’s standards</p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>Construction Coordination</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Support the construction team during build-out by answering RFIs, updating drawings, and resolving design issues in real time</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Participate in site visits, walk-throughs, and installation coordination</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Ensure design intent is carried through to final execution</p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>Client &amp; Team Collaboration</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Participate in client presentations and meetings, contributing to both design direction and communication</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Collaborate closely with project managers, designers, and fabricators</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Take ownership of assigned tasks and proactively move work forward</p><p class="text-current font-body font-bold text-sm mt-8 first:mt-0 mb-4"><strong>Studio &amp; Material Management</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Maintain organization of project files, samples, and material library</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Stay up to date on new materials, vendors, and industry trends</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium"><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">2–5 years of professional experience in <strong>interior design, architecture, or design-build environments</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Strong proficiency in <strong>Rhino, Revit, and Adobe Creative Suite</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Experience producing <strong>construction drawings and coordinating with consultants</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Strong understanding of materials, detailing, and how things are built</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Ability to manage multiple tasks and deadlines across concurrent projects</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Clear and professional communication skills, both internally and with clients/vendors</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Highly organized with strong attention to detail</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Proactive, solutions-oriented mindset with a high level of ownership</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Comfortable working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Passion for hospitality, retail, and thoughtfully executed spaces</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium"><strong>Why Bolt</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>See your work built — and built fast.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">At Bolt, your ideas don’t sit on a shelf. You’ll see your designs move quickly from concept to reality.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Be hands-on.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">You’ll be involved in every phase — from early design through construction and installation.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Work in the heart of Greenpoint.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Our studio sits in one of Brooklyn’s most creative neighborhoods, surrounded by great food and inspiring spaces.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Join a company on the rise.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">We’re growing quickly, and this role is an opportunity to take on real responsibility and grow with the company.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Build projects you’re proud of.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">From restaurants to retail environments, we care deeply about design, craft, and execution.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Work with good people.</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">We’re a tight-knit, driven team that values trust, accountability, and creative problem-solving.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium"><strong>Compensation</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $45,000–$65,000 annually, depending on experience and qualifications</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Location:</strong> In-person, Greenpoint, Brooklyn</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Schedule:</strong> Full-time</p><p class="text-curr